### 2. Renderer — Two-Key Semantic Sort

#### [MODIFY] [GameRenderer.js](file:///e:/WebGames/Onigiri/src/renderer/GameRenderer.js)

Replace the current broken sort (only isolates `flying`) with a layer-first, Y-second sort:

```js
// BEFORE — only separates flying, everything else arbitrary
s.units.sort((a,b) => (a.type==='flying'?1:0) - (b.type==='flying'?1:0))
       .forEach(u => drawUnitTopDown(ctx, u));

// AFTER — semantic layer first, Y-sort within layer
[...s.units]
  .sort((a, b) => {
    const la = a.renderLayer ?? 2;
    const lb = b.renderLayer ?? 2;
    if (la !== lb) return la - lb;  // lower layer renders first (behind)
    return a.y - b.y;              // within layer: higher Y draws on top
  })
  .forEach(u => drawUnitTopDown(ctx, u));
```

> `[...s.units]` shallow-copies before sorting to avoid mutating the live unit array mid-frame (CombatSystem iterates the same array).

