### 3. Visual Differentiation

#### [MODIFY] [drawUnits.js](file:///e:/WebGames/Onigiri/src/renderer/drawUnits.js)

**A. Cavalry spear protrusion** — Extend the current spear stub from `u.radius * 2.8` to `u.radius * 4.0` and add a solid triangle spearhead at the tip. Gives cavalry a unique horizontal silhouette that reads differently from every other unit shape (all of which are vertical ellipses or circles). Passes the Pikmin "Squint Test".

**B. Boss always-visible halo** — Add a `ctx.shadowBlur` red glow ring on the boss draw pass. Distinct from the existing `isElite` pulsing aura (which is gold/shared). The boss halo is static and intense — it burns through even when surrounded by rebels.

**C. White death flash (Doom case study)** — Units with a `deathFlash > 0` timer get a brief white overlay composited over their shape. Set `deathFlash = 0.1` in CombatSystem at the moment `hp` first drops to 0. Tick it down each frame in the renderer. This gives the player a microsecond anchor to register kills within chaos — especially valuable when a spell or Dragon Wave hits a cluster simultaneously.

**D. Suppress rebel death particles** — Currently `addParticle` fires 5 ink particles every time a Rebel dies. With 30 rebels dying in sequence this is pure visual noise. Rebels killed by standard melee skip the particle burst; their death is registered by the white flash alone.

---

### 4. Screen Shake — Boss-Only Bus Events

#### [MODIFY] [CombatSystem.js](file:///e:/WebGames/Onigiri/src/systems/CombatSystem.js)

All cavalry hits currently emit `SCREEN_SHAKE` via the event bus, which drives the CSS animation on the canvas container. 15 simultaneous charges = strobe.

**Rule**: Only boss-level impacts emit the bus event and trigger the CSS shake.

| Scenario | Before | After |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Boss telegraph | `screenShake = 0.5` + bus emit | ✅ unchanged |
| Cavalry vs. shield/boss | `screenShake = 0.1` + bus emit | ✅ unchanged (heavy collision) |
| Cavalry vs. normal target | `screenShake = 0.2` + bus emit | `screenShake = 0.05`, **no bus emit** |

